  "text": "Social exchange theory states that in social relations, people's interaction is mutual dependency and a reaction to the actions of others, not behaviors that are made by one person alone. Researchers [CITATION_1] found that the abuse management of superiors brings negative emotional experience and interpersonal relationships to lower-level employees. That is, social exchange is a reciprocal behavior.",
